16 Section 3. KRS 147.635 is amended to read as follows:
17 (1) An area planning commission created under the provisions of KRS 147.610 to
18 147.705 shall, not later than two (2) months prior to the first day of its fiscal year,
19 submit a proposed budget detailing anticipated revenues and expenditures, and a
20 proposed tax rate, to the area council for its approval on or before the first day of
21 each such fiscal year.
22 (2) The area council shall contract with an independent, reputable certified public
23 accountant to perform an audit of the records, books, and accounts of the area
24 planning commission in compliance with Section 1 of this Act[for each fiscal
25 year].
26 (3) The area planning commission and area council shall comply with the provisions of
27 KRS 65A.010 to 65A.090.
